1 A BILL for an Act to create and enact a new section to chapter 11-33, a new section to chapter
2 40-47, a new chapter to title 51, and a new section to chapter 58-03 of the North Dakota
3 Century Code, relating to blockchain technology and protection for digital asset mining.
4 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
5 SECTION 1. A new section to chapter 11-33 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
6 and enacted as follows:
7 Protection for digital asset mining.
8 1. An individual may not be prohibited, restricted, or otherwise prevented from
9 participating in digital asset mining in an area zoned for residential use if the individual
10 engaging in digital asset mining complies with all county noise ordinances.
11 2. In an area zoned for commercial use, a county may not:
12 a. Place a limit on sound decibels generated from a digital asset mining business
13 which is more restrictive than limits imposed for sound pollution in that area
14 generally.
15 b. Place restrictions on a digital asset mining business which do not apply to other
16 businesses in that area.
17 c. Change the zoning of a digital asset mining business without providing notice and
18 an opportunity for comment.
19 3. A digital asset mining business may appeal a change in zoning to the district court.
20 4. For purposes of this section:
